name: rizal taufik
text:
Pantai Tanjung Gelam merupakan salah satu pantai paling indah di Karimunjawa. Pasirnya putih dan halus, air lautnya sangat jernih dengan gradasi warna biru yang menenangkan. Suasananya cocok untuk bersantai, berenang, dan berfoto. Sunset di pantai ini sangat terkenal dan memang luar biasa indah. Akses menuju lokasi cukup mudah dan sudah ada warung-warung sederhana. Tempat yang wajib dikunjungi saat liburan ke Karimunjawa.

title: Pantai Bobby
name: Audz
text: Let me start by saying that Pantai Bobby is an absolute slice of paradise and the highlight of our Karimun Jawa trip. The journey to get there, a short and bumpy but fun ride from the main village, already feels like an adventure. But the moment you step onto the sand, every single bump is forgotten. This isn't your typical wide, sprawling beach; it's a wonderfully intimate cove, framed by lush, green hills and ancient, twisting trees that provide perfect natural shade. The water is what dreams are made of—a breathtaking mosaic of crystal-clear turquoise fading into a deeper, brilliant blue. It’s so transparent you can see small schools of fish darting around your ankles even before you wade in. The sand is brilliantly white and soft, a perfect contrast to the vibrant colors of the sea and sky. We spent hours just floating in the calm, bath-warm water, feeling completely removed from the hustle of everyday life. It’s a truly magical place that feels both pristine and peaceful.

title: Pantai Bobby
name: Nikolaus S
text:
Gorgeous beach, definitely worth visiting for the atmosphere. Unfortunately there are three key arguments that speak against it. We were there on the weekend and when the ferry arrived, a lot of people came there just to take their pictures, making it impossible to relax. The water is extremely shallow, if you want to swim there are way better options on karimjawa. Additionally there aren‘t any beachbeds, if you want to lay down you need to lay in the sand, which is not a big deal but you should be aware of it.
Great for taking pictures, but for all other aspects there are better options nearby and around the island.

text: Ottimo posto per fare una pausa pranzo, rilassarsi, godere di una bellissima vista e fare dello snorkeling. Il pesce alla griglia davvero ottimo ed abbondante al costo di 2/3 €, la conduzione dei vari chioschetti è familiare e sono tutti molto gentili. Ingresso e parcheggio all' ombra per il motorino a 0.5 €, potrete approfittare delle sedie, tavoli e sdrai artigianali in legno. C'è un piccolo promontorio che si immerge nel mare dove fare una passeggiata di 10 minuti.

title: Pantai Batu Topeng
name: Bob van Velzen
text:
Great beach for snorkeling and watching the sunset.
There is a local beach club with drinks, food and at least this time, a DJ.
Easy to reach by scooter, with enough parking.
The entry fee is 10.000rp but it is for more than 1 visit (limit unknown). Bean bags and parasol included.
The water is crystal clear and it stays very shallow for a long time.

title: Pantai Batu Topeng
name: Nikolaus S
text:
Clearly the best overall beach on the island.
The beach and waters are very clean, for the entrance fee of 10.000 rupieh you get a lot of different seats and hammocks. It is very quite during the day, most people stay one besch further west. In the evening they play loud music which is something you should be aware of. Compared to the beaches on the eastern coast of Karimunjawa the water is deeper here, so it is very enjoyable to swim.

text: Datang ke sini sendiri (tanpa travel), jalanannya cukup curam & berbatu, ada tulisan tiket masuk 25rb/orang tapi ketika datang ga ada petugas yg minta bayar. Pantainya bagus meskipun ga sepenuhnya bersih tapi masih cukup terawat & cenderung sepi. Di ujung pantai ini ada jalan setapak yg menghubungkan ke Sunset Beach & Pantai Ujung Gelam.

title: Pantai Batu Topeng
name: Alessio Pieri
text: Collegata direttamente a piedi alla più nota Sunset Beach (solo che qui non si paga il parcheggio). Questa spiaggia è una piccola chicca di sabbia bianca, silenziosa e alberata. Offerta bar/ristoranti scarna (spesso risultano chiusi o hanno già terminato tutto). Permane anche qui la grande piaga del sud-est asiatico: rifiuti un po’ ovunque. Sì, anche in acqua. Non meravigliatevi se troverete spazzatura ovunque (anche in acqua). Purtroppo vi è pochissima sensibilità verso il problema in questa area del mondo. Resta comunque una spiaggia bellissima e molto godibile

title: Pantai Batu Topeng

Perfect!!!

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: Lautra Islora
text:
Sebaiknnya jangan kemari saat air laut pasang. Jalan menuju pantai ini bersisian dengan pantai dan laut yang menggenangi jalan saat pasang. Menutup akses jalan dan menjadikannya gembur sehingga ban kendaraan rawan terjebak dalam pasir.

Namun secara umum, pantai ini menarik untuk dikunjungi. Ayunan, gazebo dan warung-warung disekitar pantai menyediakan cukup camilan untuk berlama-lama di tempat ini.

Jika punya waktu agak longgar, coba untuk mendaki bukit. Pemandangan laut lepas dan batu-batu karang yang membentuk bukit menjadikan tempat ini tidak kalah fotogenik meskipun untuk mencapainya dibutuhkan perjuangan ekstra.

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: Ardha Kesuma
text: Terdapat area santai dengan bangku dan ayunan, lengkap dengan warung makan khas jajanan pantai. Menariknya Annora, terdapat bukit di tengah-tengah laut. Bisa mendaki untuk melihat laut dari atas bukit, dan seolah menemukan pantai-pantai lain dari beberapa sisi lereng bukitnya. Bagi yang ingin mandi pantai, disarankan oleh penduduk setempat untuk datang pada setelah pukul 3 sore, karena air laut surut, dan terdapat daratan baru di--agak--tengah laut.

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: Bang Tora
text:
Spot pertama yang dikunjungi setelah menginjakkan kaki di Pulau Karimunjawa. Pantai nya unik, bersih, dan tertata rapi. HTM 10k/orang. Fasilitas parkir motor dan mobil luas, toilet bersih, warung2 penjual makanan dan minuman sudah tersedia. Area pantainya ditata rapi dengan banyak bangku duduk dari kayu, ayunan yang banyak tersebar.

Spot unik lainnya adalah Bukit Love Annora Hill, sebuah tanjung kecil dengan view lautan lepas dan tenang. Disini view lautnya hijau tosca dan jernih. Sayangnya diujung sini banyak terdapat sampah bekas pengunjung yang datang, padahal sudah disediakan tempat sampah. Semoga kedepannya pengunjung bisa sadar akan kebersihan di pantai cantik ini.

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: ayundahaha
text:
Akses ya dari jalan utama di Karimunjawa lalu masuk jalan makadam, terus tanah dan pasir pantai. Retribusi murah banget, sy agak lupa antara 5/10rb masuknya.

Di pantai tsb ada bukit, naiknya gak jauh kok, bukit jg gak terlalu tinggi. Tp pemandangan oke bgt kl dr atas bukit. Kata guide lokal, kalau mau foto di bukit baiknya mulai dr jam12. Supaya air terlihat lebih biru. Tp memang sepertinya kebanyakan pantai di Karimunjawa garis pantainya agak naik, entah krn pemanasan global atau krn memang sedang pasang. Tp dpt cerita jg dr ibu yg jaga warung di pantai anora. Akses jalan yg lbh dalam ketutup pasir karena angin dan ombak besar bbrp waktu lalu.

Pantainya agak sepi dan bersih. Sy kemarin blm sempat ciblon karena cuaca krg mendukung.

Oh iya, ini ada salah satu foto untk akses masuk ke pantai anora. Ada jalan batu jg, jd perlu Hati2 jg dlm berkendara.

name: WAWICAKSONO, Adv Storyteller
text:
Pantai di seputar pulau Karimunjawa yang mungkin kurang begitu populer tapi menawarkan pemandangan pantai laut biru dan bebatuan karang yang alami dan mempesona.

Boleh jadi mungkin karena transportasi ke sini memerlukan perjuangan yang tidak ringan, menjadikan pantai ini kerap sepi dan lengang.

Bagaimana pun juga tekad untuk sejenak terombang-ambing gelombang dengan perahu boat untuk sampai kesini tak membuat setiap orang mau berkungjung ke sini.

Padahal tentu saja perjuangan tidak mengkhiañati hasil. Berakit-rakit ke hulu, nikmati pemandangan indah pantai Annora kemudian.

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: Dea
text:
Annora Beach is pretty gorgeous. It has white and grey sand, but mostly grey. The locals sell foods and drinks, such as : grilled fish, fried banana, mendoan, bakwan, and kelapa muda (coconut). There are two bathrooms, not really clean but usable. You can rent a motorcycle from the locals to ride around Annora Beach. It has swings to play or take a photo. Sadly, the beach is not as clean as Bobby beach. There are trashes laying around.
But overall it's a good beach for vacation and resting (not for sunbathing). Would recommend it to others.

title: Pantai Annora ꦥꦤ꧀ꦠꦻꦄꦤꦺꦴꦫ
name: usman maulana Ismail
text:
terletak di Dusun Cikmas, Pulau Karimunjawa, Kepulauan Karimunjawa. Pantai yang memiliki banyak ayunan ini cukup unik dan cukup lengkap, pasalnya pantai ini juga mempunyai "gosong" dan bukit indah dengan view luas.

Pantai Annora terletak diujung utara pulau Karimunjawa yang berbatas dengan pulau Kemujan, disekitarpantai Annora juga terdapat pantai Yamin dan Pantai Kemloko.

Pantai Annora memiliki luas yang lumayan besar karena memiliki 2 pantai yang dipisahkan oleh bukit yang menyimpan view indah pantai Annora dari atas, dan pantai ini sepertinya belum menjadi milik perseorangan / grup ( semoga tidak di jual ) karena masih sangat alami dan potensi pantai ini cukup besar untuk menjadi idola baru di Karimunjawa.

Untuk menuju ke Pantai Annora, dari lapangan/alun-alun Karimunjawa cukup berkendara menuju ke pulau Kemujan, sebelum sampai pulau kemujan nanti akan ada palang denah lokasi Dusun Cikmas, di denah tersebut terdapat rute menuju pantai Yamin dan pantai Kemloko, disitu tidak dituliskan pantai Annora

title: Pantai Kanjen
name: Anita Gomoliszewska
text:
I’m writing this review with a painful heart - do not visit this place if you care about the turtles! We visited hoping that this is a turtle sanctuary since it’s somehow advertised as being associated with the “national park” so we thought perhaps this is a real one.

We got charged 150k per person for the boat to get there. As soon as we got there we saw big turtles enclosed in a net in the ocean in terrible condition obviously sick, covered with slimy green growth. These were years old turtles, obviously old enough to be released, even if turtle well being was actually the goal of this place. The “guide” said they’re kept there “to show there are two colours of the turtles” which, well, made it clear upfront what this place is.

The turtles on the beach are kept in plastic boxes, hundreds of tiny ones in one box, kept there until tourists pay to release one. There were dead ones floating in between the alive ones. Plenty of older turtles kept in these boxes their whole lives for nothing apart from a show for tourists! The “guides”were lifting them out spinning them in the air & showing to the tourists with the turtles being obviously terrified. Money for releasing a turtle is paid to the boat driving person who obviously has nothing to do with conservation.

We left with painful hearts & spoke to our hosts on Karimunjawa and they confirmed - it’s not a sanctuary it’s a business! Eggs are stolen from beaches & sold to this place, then they’re kept in captivity until tourists pay for the experience of releasing one ….

This place has nothing to do with a sanctuary - it is yet another place in Indonesia where nature & animals are cruelly used for the financial gains of locals. Simply shameful!

title: Pantai Kanjen

text: ich war nicht hier, habe ehrlich gesagt nichts Positives über diesen Ort gehört, eher im Gegenteil und dass es nicht um Tierschutz sondern eher um Tourismus und Geld geht und wenn man gegen Bezahlung Schildkröten freilassen kann, ich denke das sagt ja wohl alles🤷‍♂️

title: Pantai Kanjen
name: Federico Bettinardi
text: Sconsigliamo a tutti coloro che amano gli animali questa esperienza. Siamo andati in questo posto credendo fosse una specie di centro per accrescimento tartarughe e recupero di quelle malate o infortunate, gestito da personale professionale e attento, che ci spiegasse anche qualcosa visto che abbiamo pagato il biglietto. In realtà  ci siamo trovati in una trovata per fare soldi a costo zero con nessuno che parla inglese, solo idioma stretto. Ci mostrano  6 vasche, con poca acqua puzzolente piena di escrementi  con le tartarughe da piccole a  qualche stadio di accrescimento in più. Gli animali piccoli erano centinaia per vasca con poco cibo tanto che si attaccavano a vicenda e tante morte lasciate lì a galleggiare in mezzo alle altre, quelle più grandi erano poche , con i gusci pieni di melma verde. Dopo pochi minuti ci hanno chiesto se volevamo pagare un extra per prendere una piccola tartarughina e buttarla nell'oceano  e fare foto e video.... squallido

title: Pantai Kanjen
name: Naly agnes
text: Au départ, nous sommes contents d'apprendre que les œufs de tortue sont récupérés pour permettre leur éclosion. Mais en voyant que les touristes peuvent toucher les bébés, voire payer pour les mettre dans l'eau, nous sommes scandalisés. Il ne s'agit pas de les sauver, mais de se faire de l'argent sans se soucier du bien-être ou de la survie de ces animaux. C'est une honte ! Nous comprendrions mieux qu'il y ait un droit d'entrée, si cela permettait VRAIMENT de sauvegarder les tortues, mais pas ce cirque hypocrite. Ne participez pas à cette mascarade.

Some activities can be done here like grilling fish, enjoying the white sand or snorkeling around the jetty.

text:
Dermaga di Batu Lawang tergolong sebagai dermaga yang cukup besar dan bagus sehingga kapal besar pun bisa merapat ke dermaga ini. Warna biru selalu berada di sekeliling kita, dimana-mana biru Subhanallah. Waktu itu kita sudah terlalu lapar jadi kita makan roti tawar yang kita bawa sebagai pengganjal perut.
Binokuler juga bisa berfungsi untuk melihat pulau diseberang sana, langsung aja dengan perbesaran lensa yang agak lumayan namun terbatas juga pandangan penglihatan dengan menggunakan alat tersebut kita amati pulau-pulau tersebut. Pulau-pulau yang terlihat kecil-kecil pasti di tempat itu menyimpan beribu keindahan. Indah nian tempat ini Subhanallah 👍👍👍

title: Pantai Kanjen
name: Prasetyo Budi Widagdo
text:
Kawasan ini adalah zona inti Taman Nasional Karimunjawa yang dijadikan sebagai obyek wisata terbatas. di lokasi ini terdapat perlindungan untuk telur-telur penyu di ruangan khusus untuk menghindari predator dan jika beruntung wisatawan dapat melepasliarkan tukik ke laut bersama penjaga.
Pantai ini menjadi salah satu pilihan untuk penyu mendarat karena pasir yang halus dan hangat serta minim predator karena daya dukung lingkungan yang rendah akibat sistem DAS yang sangat sempit. Bagi wisatawan, pasir halus ini dapat dibuat istana pasir ,,, :D

The turnoff to the beach is small, so be on the lookout.

Take anti mosquito cream as you will be 'attacked' by them when you stop.

It is a short walk down to the beach. You will pay 5 000 IDR for parking.

The beach has beautiful white sand and there are many places to snorkel.

There are many places for you to take photos, so don't forget your camera.

Sdraio di legno e posti per rilassarsi sono già presenti nella struttura. Il personale é molto cordiale e c'è la possibilità di ordinare bevande o cibo cucinato sul momento

Jika ke karimun wajib ke pantai ini karena benar2 belum banyak yang tau. Perjalanan memang cukup jauh 30 menit drai pusat kota tapi percayalah begitu parkir motor, matamu akan terpuaskan dengan pemandangannya.

text:
해변에서 배를 빌려 조금만 들어가면 산호군락지가 펼쳐집니다.
배빌리는 금액 얼마 안하니 한 두시간정도 배를 타고 둘러보면서 돌고래도 보고 참치낚시도 하고 일주일 내내 여기만 갔네요
비싼돈 주고 종일 투어해서 보는 것과 다르지 않으니 꼭 한번 체험해보세요.
보홀이나 꼬리뻬등 여러 곳 가보았는데.. 여기 산호군락이 최고였습니다.
다음에 기회가 되서 다시 갔을 때 지금과 같은 환경이 꼭 보존되었으면 합니다.

title: Sunset Beach
name: Faith E
text:
Very pretty beach as well as the adjacent ones. Leftmost Tanjung Gelam is more for waterspots and photoshoots, sunset beach is for the sunset and eating, and Batu Topeng is a great place for chilling out and swimming as the water is deeper here. Theres also a volleyball net.

You can walk between all three very easily. The beaches are super clean and have all the necessary amenities.

In September I found them to be almost empty during the day (even on a Saturday!) but they get busier around 3 onwards as sunset approached.

title: Pancuran Beach
name: Ahmed Ziauddin Qoyyum
text:
Most Karimun visitor choose the famous Bobby or Karina in the north but i prefer this beach.. The first free-entry beach on south-east side of Karimun Jawa Island. The entrance is like going downhill until the parking space and then walking downstairs to the beach area. There is only one restaurant with quite good playlist. If you are lucky you can connect to their wifi.. I think their highlight menu is fried pineapple..

I visited this beach twice : for lunch and sunrise view.. Since it was weekday, there was less people. It's like having the beach for yourself, when it's getting crowded then the time to leave..

It is a swimming/snorkling/kayaking/paddling spot, so you can enjoy those activities here.. You can find another hidden beach in the north, just next to the corner. There is a path between the rock..

Toilet is available. Next to the restaurant..

name: Paulina F
text: Some parts of the beach are full of plastic and random shacks that totally ruined the charm of this beautiful place. It must’ve been a paradise before people took it over, but I get that for many, it’s a way to make a living, so I don’t blame them and I must understand their reality. Still, it looks pretty sad. The nature itself is beautifu and a color of the water is magical. The amount of trash is also kind of shocking. I wish the Indonesian government would do something to protect this amazing place because it is special, nature is your real treasure.

title: Sunset Beach
name: Ammar Syah Roif
text:
This place is wonderful! as well as to get a sunset (such as it's name), it has a nice atmosphere, and always has a comfort feelings around. But as usual, Indonesian are still lacking at how do they maintenance things, such trash (luckily, the trash at the sand beach was less noticeable), sustaining useful facilities, and awareness about many of stagnant water that causes mosquitoes.

The best way to enjoy those chilling atmosphere, those splash of ocean water, and bird chirping is when the beach is not that crowded. My fams are lucky that we arrived at the right time and date.

9/10.

title: Pancuran Beach
name: B
text:
I visited this place by walking from near the dock of Karimun island. It's pretty far but still managable. The beach was just destroyed by the wave days before. Nobody was there besides 2 locals who managed the small store there, and they were cleaning up the beach. The beach was so dirty so many trash was there when I visited June 27th 2022 .
It's a small beach but because it was so quiet, it feels so cozy. There is a small stream that flows to the beach, I guess that's why they called it Pancuran Beach. I believe it might be way more beautiful before it was hit by huge waves. Anyways I saw a biawak there

title: Pancuran Beach
name: erica de vecchi
text:
Spiaggia a pagamento, 10000 rupie a persona. Credevo che i soldi dati da noi turisti occidentali servissero a mantenere il luogo in cui vivono (e tutti noi viviamo) pulito.
Quello che invece mi sono ritrovata dinnanzi, dietro al velo di perfezione paradisiaca di un mare cristallino, dietro alle sdraio, agli ombrelloni e bar, è stato un mare di plastica seppellito sotto alla spiaggia a giusto 2 metri di distanza da quella attrezzata.

Bottiglie di plastica, zaini di plastica, ciabatte di gomma, sacchetti di plastica nascosti sotto la sabbia candida.

Questo è stato lo scenario visto e rivisto in differenti luoghi dell'Indonesia. Facciata di perfezione che nasconde assenza di rispetto per il loro paese meraviglioso e per tutti noi che viviamo in questo pianeta.
Rifiuti gettati per le strade, per i boschi.

Non è oro tutto quel che luccica. Molto spesso non è altro che plastica.

title: Pantai Bobby
name: blub tief
text:
Ein schöner Strand, jedoch wie bei fast allen gepflegten Stränden auf Karimunjawa muss man hier 10k IDR Eintritt bezahlen. Es gibt ein WC, "Gebetsraum" bzw eher ein Gazebo, Sitzmöglichkeiten, einen Warung der Essen u d Trinken verkauft und ca 7 Schaukeln die gratis sind und teilweise hoch oben an Palmen befestigt sind. Tagsüber kann es relativ voll werden und die meisten wollen Fotos von sich mit den Schaukeln und anderen Spots machen.
Weiter draußen gibt es ein paar schöne Plätze zum Schnorcheln und wenn man motiviert ist, könnte man auch zu der kleinen vorgelagerten Insel schwimmen.
Vermutlich auch ein guter Strand für den Sonnenaufgang, hab ich aber nicht getestet und abends wenn das Wasser seichter wird, könnte man auch zum Pantai Karina rübergehen.

Da ich öfters Rezensionen gelesen habe, dass man ein Boot zur Schildkrötenaufzuchtstation mieten kann, ich habe ehrlich gesagt nichts Positives über diesen Ort gehört, eher im Gegenteil und dass es nicht um Tierschutz sondern eher Tourismus und Geld geht und wenn man gegen Bezahlung Schildkröten freilassen kann, ich denke das sagt ja wohl alles🤷‍♂️

title: Pantai Legon Lele
name: Anova Fatimah
text: After visiting Bobby Beach, I stopped by Legon Lele and was struck by how quiet it was—almost eerily so, especially when alone. The sunrise here is also hard to catch, as it's blocked by a hill. One of the beach's main features is a sunken ship, but the beach itself isn’t very clean due to its bay-like shape, where trash tends to collect, and it’s not cleaned frequently. The road to the beach is accessible by motorbike, though cars may have a bit of trouble navigating it. Additionally, there’s a hill in the area, and the local sources of clean water comes from this very hill.

title: Pantai Legon Lele
name: Bang Tora
text:
Bisa jadi pantai ini kotor. Yaa kotor dan tumpukan sampah di sepanjang garis pantai. Jalanannya agak becek, belum terbangun sempurna. Seakan pantai yang ditinggal dan tidak dirawat. Namun kalau diamati benar2, pantai ini cantik loh. Kontras dengan saudaranya, si Pantai Bobby yang berair hijau tosca yang ramai dikunjungi pengunjung. Pantai Si Legon Lele terlihat menarik dengan caranya sendiri. Warna kekuningan. Yah. Kekuningan kaya air kencing. Namun jangan salah. Itu adalah air dari pohon bakau. Jika diperhatikan, warna kuning keemasan nya itu unik. Waktu kesini dan berjalan mengexplore pesisirnya, yang disuguhkan kepada kami adalah warna air kuning keemasannya. Kami tidak terlalu peduli dengan saking banyaknya sampah yang berserakan. Namun yang kami tangkap adalah Si Cantik Legon Lele menyambut kami dengan wujud dirinya sendiri. Beda. Apa adanya.

Di seberang pantai nampak bangunan semacam rumah terapung yang mengingatkan kami kepada Ora Beach di Maluku. Semoga kedepannya Pantai cantik ini ada yang peduli. Peduli pada warna dirinya yang beda. Peduli pada kuning keemasan warna air nya. Kuning keemasan kejayaan. Semoga sampah2 jadi hilang dari pantai secantik ini.

Apalagi tdk sering dibersihkan. Jalan masih bs diakses dgn motor, mobil agak ngepres. Tp kmrn ketemu penduduk lokal yg bawa mobil dr arah Legon Lele jg sih..

Di legon lele ada bukit, dapet cerita dr karyawan hostel kalau salah satu sumber air bersih dari bukit di Legon Lele itu.

text: Pantai Tanjung Gelam adalah salah satu pantai terindah di Karimunjawa! Pasir putih yang lembut dan air laut yang jernih membuatnya sempurna untuk berenang, bersantai dan bermain. Kamu bisa main kano dan jetsky, tentunya berbayar. Suasana di sini sangat tenang dan damai.

title: Pantai Tanjung Gelam
name: Geraldy Previanza
text: Salah satu pantai terbaik di karimun jawa! Ini spot yang paling bagus untuk lihat sunset. Selain menikmati indahnya matahari terbenam, juga bisa main jetski dan watersport lainnya. Menikmat sore dengan gorengan di stall kecil sembari mendengarkan air laut yang menyusuri pasir pantai. Recommended banget masih bersih juga 👍🏼👍🏼

title: Pantai Bobby
name: Nukepositive
text: To get here, you need to go down a brick road that seems to lead nowhere. But you'll know it when you see it. It's a great beach for kids. The water is very shallow with no waves. There's swings, tree houses, and hammocks. The main thing not kid-friendly is the usual clientele smokes a lot. I just relaxed in a hammock here since I'd been driving a motorbike all day, and it was very peaceful.
